10.26	Leitner_System	Leitner system	The Leitner system is a widely used method to efficiently use flashcards that was proposed by the German science journalist Sebastian Leitner in the 1970s. It is a simple implementation of the principle of spaced repetition, where cards are reviewed at increasing interval.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/34/Flashcard.png
